doc.after: Cheshire is a ceremonial county in the North West of England Chester is the county town and formerly gave its name to the county The largest town is Warrington and other major towns include Congleton Crewe Ellesmere Port Macclesfield Northwich Runcorn Sandbach Widnes Wilmslow and Winsford The county is administered as four unitary authorities
